select add_rule_data ('default','','','default','','','','','','VMware ESXi Version 5 Virtual Machine',' III - Administrative Sensitive ','ESXI5-VM-000001','C-46717r4_chk','Virtual machines (VMs) that have a greater risk of being exploited or attacked, or that run applications known to potentially consume resources must be constrained. From the vSphere Client/vCenter, select the Datacenter/host. Right-click the VM, select Edit Settings to check the virtual machine"s memory and/or CPU shares, limits, and/or reservation(s). Appropriate values must be set for memory, CPU, advanced CPU, and disk variables. Care must be taken to ensure that the settings do not hamper dynamic resource allocation and management proper to virtualization systems.\n\nIf any host VMs do not have share, limit, and/or reservation setpoints initialized, as appropriate to their respective levels of the risk of exploit or attack, this is a finding.','Imported data from UCF - DISA') from dual;
